                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 26, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Under Revised Statutes, consuls have extraterritorial jurisdiction over citizens
                    accused of insurrection or rebellion against Turkey, or of less offense of
                    similar character. Guedjian’s act seems to have been political conspiracy with
                    enemies of Turkey in England. Trial by Turkish court without notice to consul at
                    Beirut or consular agent at Aleppo was in violation of international right, and
                    should be annulled. You should ask that he be brought to Constantinople. If
                    accused of insurrection or rebellion committed in Turkish dominion, you or
                    consul should insist upon trying him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
